1
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:32,217
-I mean--
-Hey.

2
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:34,427
-I...
-Did I...

3
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:56,324
What are you doing?

4
00:01:57,909 --> 00:01:58,743
I'm sorry.

5
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:00,328
I'm sorry, Yeon-seo.

6
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:15,969
Darn it!

7
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:24,435
Come here.

8
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:26,938
-This way.
-It's raining!

9
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:28,982
-Go to the side!
-It's raining!

10
00:02:29,399 --> 00:02:30,942
Why are you doing this to me?

11
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:39,951
Thank you.

12
00:02:40,785 --> 00:02:41,911
I almost got caught.

13
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,165
My wings!

14
00:02:53,172 --> 00:02:55,133
Goodness, my brother.

15
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:58,094
Please come to your senses.

16
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:00,471
That jerk.

17
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:03,057
That pervert. That phony religious jerk.

18
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:31,252
I'm sorry I'm late.

19
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:35,048
Where's Mr. Kim?

20
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:38,509
Let's go.

21
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:06,829
I'm fine.

22
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,581
Summer rain can give you a cold too.

23
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:11,334
And you get a fever when you catch a cold.

24
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:12,794
Do I?

25
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,213
You're wrong.

26
00:04:16,047 --> 00:04:18,132
You get a fever when you catch a cold.

27
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:19,217
Come here.

28
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,222
Stay still.

29
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:31,604
You shouldn't get sick.

30
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:36,192
From now on, you must never
get sick or injured.

31
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:38,820
You shouldn't be alone either.

32
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:47,120
A Pilates instructor will come over
in the morning.

33
00:04:47,203 --> 00:04:48,288
Check your condition.

34
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:51,082
Do cardio exercise and weight training
in the morning and stretch after that.

35
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:52,417
You'll start getting back in shape.

36
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,377
Take a breath.

37
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:55,878
Why are you in a hurry?

38
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,505
You need to prepare yourself for war.

39
00:04:57,922 --> 00:04:58,965
From tomorrow,

40
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:01,384
no, from now on, it's war.

41
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:02,385
I can take care of myself.

42
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:04,012
Then why did you get drenched?

43
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:07,181
You're the one who dropped the bomb.

44
00:05:07,265 --> 00:05:10,435
You announced your own comeback.

45
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:13,104
A dancer is someone
who speaks with their body.

46
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:14,689
I regained my sight,

47
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:17,358
and nothing is wrong with
my body and mind.

48
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,776
I will show you more in detail

49
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:21,696
through my dance at my return performance.

50
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:25,074
Are you sure you're physically
and mentally healthy?

51
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:28,911
Just look at me.

52
00:05:30,496 --> 00:05:31,831
Imagine that it's just

53
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:34,000
you and me in this world.

54
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:38,212
Yes, I am.

55
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,048
I'm completely fine.

56
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:52,101
People are more excited to hear about
others' failure more than their success.

57
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:55,021
Those who applauded your comeback

58
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,273
will be the first ones

59
00:05:57,356 --> 00:05:59,150
to criticize you if you fail.

60
00:05:59,817 --> 00:06:01,903
You're on the edge of a cliff.

61
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,654
Whether it be a cliff
or the fiery pits of hell,

62
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:06,324
it's me who's there, not you.

63
00:06:06,407 --> 00:06:08,659
I'm the one in charge of
your comeback performance.

64
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:11,829
If you fail, it will humiliate me too.

65
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:13,414
Two weeks.

66
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:15,708
I'll give you two weeks.

67
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:16,918
Get your body back in shape

68
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:18,753
and receive my approval first.

69
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:20,129
If you fail,

70
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:22,590
Keum Ni-na will be
the prima ballerina of Fantasia.

71
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:24,425
One week.

72
00:06:27,011 --> 00:06:28,137
That's all I need.

73
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:32,558
Ni-na. Where are you?

74
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:33,810
Ni-na.

75
00:06:37,355 --> 00:06:38,356
Ni-na.

76
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:43,486
Why are you out here?

77
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:45,029
Ru-na.

78
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:49,575
Director Ji.

79
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:52,078
I have something to tell you.

80
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:53,955
Next time. I have an appointment.

81
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,374
Are you meeting Yeon-seo?

82
00:06:58,751 --> 00:07:00,545
That's none of your business.

83
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:06,008
Don't go.

84
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:07,510
Keum Ni-na.

85
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,303
You told me to be selfish.

86
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,056
I'm going to

87
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:14,392
like you.

88
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:16,144
No.

89
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:17,979
I already do.

90
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:25,111
I'll pretend that I didn't hear that.

91
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:27,905
It was since that night.

92
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:30,992
That night when you touched my ankle.

93
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:37,748
It felt like a big rock
had fallen into my heart.

94
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,127
Why today?

95
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:43,463
Your biggest rival announced

96
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:46,090
her comeback after a three-year gap.

97
00:07:46,174 --> 00:07:47,300
But on a day like this,

98
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:48,885
you decided to listen

99
00:07:49,218 --> 00:07:52,346
to your useless emotions
and confessed to me.

100
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:54,223
I'm disappointed in you.

101
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:55,766
"Useless"?

102
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,435
Let's not waste any time.

103
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,980
I'm not Prince Charming
like you think I am.

104
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,440
Then you can tell me.

105
00:08:02,523 --> 00:08:04,192
That's what I'm most curious about.

106
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:08,237
What kind of person are you?

107
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:09,655
I'm an evil person.

108
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:13,326
I'm beyond what you can imagine or handle.

109
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:15,495
I'm very evil.

110
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:22,627
I shouldn't have told him. I was too rash.

111
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:24,545
When Yeon-seo returns,

112
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:26,797
I will become a shadow again.

113
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:29,342
And when that happens,
I thought he wouldn't

114
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:31,385
look at me even more than he does now.

115
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:32,929
I agree with him.

116
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:37,558
You already act like a shadow,
so who will take notice of you?

117
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:39,352
Why are you being so scary?

118
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:41,521
Where's your pride? Are you not angry?

119
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:44,774
You were looked down on as a ballerina
and also as a woman.

120
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:47,568
That makes me so upset.

121
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:51,155
But you're just being childish and crying.

122
00:08:51,405 --> 00:08:52,573
Stop being a baby.

123
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:54,784
No one's going to fix this for you.

124
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:10,925
I said, go. Please go.

125
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:12,927
There's no emergency.
The rain has stopped.

126
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,637
It's getting late, so go.

127
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,846
Don't get kicked out again.

128
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:26,232
I feel like I did something wrong.

129
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:28,526
Is it possible for an angel
to feel guilty?

130
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:30,403
Can an angel commit a sin?

131
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,498
Answer me. Who are you?

132
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:47,253
I'm Kim Dan.

133
00:09:47,336 --> 00:09:48,546
Don't tell me your human name.

134
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:49,714
Tell me your real name.

135
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:51,382
What are you?

136
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,469
I'm Angel Dan.

137
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,554
That's right.

138
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:59,223
Then you must know
what'll happen to an angel if he gives up

139
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:01,309
on his mission and commit a sin.

140
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:06,063
I didn't commit a sin.
It just feels like I did.

141
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:07,231
"Feels"?

142
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:09,942
You don't want to go up there, do you?

143
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:13,279
Would you like to
turn into dust right here?

144
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:14,488
Are you threatening me?

145
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,157
Are you an angel or a thug?

146
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:23,914
Come on!

147
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:35,468
I still have time left!

148
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:38,012
An angel should only be obedient.

149
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:40,389
If you have other intentions,
you'll only be doomed.

150
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,850
Just like how you can differentiate
what's holy from what's worldly,

151
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,644
and a good man from an evil one,

152
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,063
remember who is before you.

153
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:50,816
Just like how you've led cats and dogs,

154
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:53,611
it's the same for that woman, got it?

155
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:14,340
KIM DAN

156
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:23,284
Excuse me. I'd like a bottle of soju.

157
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:34,628
Thank you.

158
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:44,972
What brings you here?

159
00:12:45,055 --> 00:12:46,432
What about you?

160
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:48,392
Why are you here at this hour?

161
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,395
Someone told me

162
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:53,981
that it is the best remedy
when my heart is on fire.

163
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:57,109
Okay, then.

164
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:02,740
Your heart is on fire?

165
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,502
Just quit if this is
how you'll do your job.

166
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,671
-Pardon?
-I'll get you a new job.

167
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:19,173
I can get you a better paying job.

168
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:22,510
A job that can accommodate your needs.

169
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:24,970
What if I say I don't want to?

170
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:26,847
"I don't want to"? Not, "I can't"?

171
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,557
-Why not?
-If I have to get fired,

172
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:30,476
I want it to be Yeon-seo who fires me.

173
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:33,479
This isn't your business to meddle with.

174
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,147
You said you were going to help me.

175
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:38,817
Have you forgotten
what you need to do? Or...

176
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:42,613
Or did you have a change of heart?

177
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,907
I keep my promises.

178
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:48,786
I'm going to fix you up
with Yeon-seo myself.

179
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:50,120
"Ms. Lee".

180
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,543
You keep calling her by her name.

181
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:56,752
That's been bothering me a lot.

182
00:13:57,461 --> 00:13:59,171
Seeing how you drop your
honorifics to your boss,

183
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,756
I doubt that you're good at your job.

184
00:14:02,841 --> 00:14:04,176
Why are you getting angry at me?

185
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,055
I've already seen her alone

186
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:10,558
in the rain twice.

187
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:13,894
You were worried because Yeon-seo

188
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:15,980
was alone.

189
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:18,107
Is that why you got angry?

190
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:20,067
Listen.

191
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:22,570
I'm asking why you're not
doing your job right...

192
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:26,198
What are you doing?

193
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:28,576
You're running a fever.

194
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:31,495
And your pupils are shaky too.

195
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:34,915
And you're nervous.

196
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,210
I was right. You're definitely angry.

197
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,966
I'm all for worrying about Ms. Lee.

198
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:45,092
I'm all for it,

199
00:14:45,175 --> 00:14:48,095
but I'll take care of my job myself.

200
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,148
What was that?

201
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:03,819
She's a puppy or a kitty.

202
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:07,072
She's a pine tree or grass.

203
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:08,991
Yeon-seo is just a client.

204
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:11,160
After I make Yeon-seo fall in love,

205
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:13,621
I will go back up there no matter what.

206
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:35,976
I wasn't angry.

207
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:41,607
No. Actually, I was.

208
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:43,901
I'm so livid.

209
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:47,696
You were worried because Yeon-seo

210
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:49,281
was alone.

211
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:50,574
Is that why you got angry?

212
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:53,869
It's because of ballet.

213
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:55,704
I barely

214
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:58,040
managed to get you this far.

215
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:00,084
I just need to put you on the stage.

216
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,629
Then, I can keep my promise to you.

217
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:07,132
But how could you fall for
a mere secretary?

218
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:23,565
Why are all the curtains closed?

219
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:26,568
It's so dark in here.

220
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:36,620
Ms. Lee.

221
00:16:39,164 --> 00:16:40,624
What are you doing here?

222
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:45,212
Did you stay up all night?

223
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:47,381
Absence without notice
and leaving the workplace

224
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:49,925
-can be reasons for dismissal, right?
-Are you talking about Dan?

225
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,468
Did something happen last night?

226
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:52,594
I know what your wishes are.

227
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:55,347
I will grant your wish.

228
00:16:58,475 --> 00:17:00,269
Because I listened to you...

229
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:02,563
What did I do?

230
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:06,233
I see. You're talking about Dan?

231
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:08,736
-Him having a crush on you?
-He doesn't.

232
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:09,945
Apparently he doesn't.

233
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,114
Did you ask that to his face?

234
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:13,949
Of course, he'd deny that.

235
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:15,868
No, I didn't do that.

236
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:21,790
From now on, please refrain from

237
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:23,667
spreading and making groundless rumors.

238
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,630
There's no way my instincts are wrong.

239
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,675
Also, fire that jerk.

240
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:33,052
For good this time.

241
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:34,553
Good morning.

242
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:40,100
Did you sleep well?

243
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:41,185
Ms. Jung.

244
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:44,271
Tell him that staying out overnight can be
a reason for his dismissal.

245
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,692
Something urgent came up.

246
00:17:49,026 --> 00:17:50,360
Please tell her that I'm sorry.

247
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:54,281
I'm sorry, Ms. Lee.

248
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,659
What's wrong with you?
Why are you so polite?

249
00:17:58,077 --> 00:17:59,787
I've been overstepping my boundaries.

250
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,498
I will focus on my work from now on.

251
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:06,376
I'm glad to hear that.

252
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:08,670
I'm going to the studio to practice.

253
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,693
I have something to tell you.

254
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:35,864
Go ahead.

255
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:39,827
Last night...

256
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:45,290
I was...

257
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:55,926
I'm sorry about last night.

258
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:57,845
Please forget what happened.

259
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:03,350
What do you mean?

260
00:19:03,725 --> 00:19:05,394
Nothing happened last night between us.

261
00:19:06,353 --> 00:19:07,354
You and I...

262
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,649
Right. Nothing happened.

263
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:12,401
Nothing at all.

264
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:13,861
Something happened between us.

265
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:15,237
No, nothing happened.

266
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,488
No, it did.

267
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:19,408
What's your point, you jerk?

268
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:20,909
You told me to forget about it.

269
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,328
I'm trying to pretend that nothing
happened between us and move on.

270
00:19:23,453 --> 00:19:24,371
Are you that clueless?

271
00:19:24,454 --> 00:19:25,372
Can't you play along?

272
00:19:25,455 --> 00:19:27,207
I can't lie that nothing happened
when it did.

273
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:28,417
To pretend that--

