540
00:38:20,089 --> 00:38:22,049
I have to help her find her love, right?

541
00:38:22,383 --> 00:38:24,343
But does that have to be
love between a human

542
00:38:25,177 --> 00:38:26,887
and another human?

543
00:38:28,931 --> 00:38:30,016
It has to be, right?

544
00:38:34,937 --> 00:38:36,856
I somehow ended up kissing her.

545
00:38:37,231 --> 00:38:39,025
Ever since then,
my heart beats uncontrollably

546
00:38:39,233 --> 00:38:40,860
as if it's broken.

547
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:43,863
And then sometimes,
I suddenly feel suffocated.

548
00:38:44,238 --> 00:38:45,573
Rib asked me

549
00:38:46,407 --> 00:38:48,326
if I have feelings

550
00:38:48,951 --> 00:38:50,244
for Yeon-seo.

551
00:38:50,453 --> 00:38:51,454
Goodness.

552
00:38:51,704 --> 00:38:53,372
What am I going to do with you?

553
00:38:58,627 --> 00:38:59,628
Let's see.

554
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:01,756
It was about 15 years ago.

555
00:39:02,465 --> 00:39:05,259
There was an angel
who was in charge of the arts.

556
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:12,892
He took on the human form

557
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:15,144
and was given a mission

558
00:39:15,478 --> 00:39:16,896
to inspire artists.

559
00:39:38,709 --> 00:39:41,003
Just when he was growing tired of
bad-tempered artists,

560
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:43,172
he met this person.

561
00:40:45,526 --> 00:40:47,194
I heard there's a chance
you can get confused.

562
00:40:47,736 --> 00:40:49,363
That angel who was in charge of the arts

563
00:40:50,322 --> 00:40:52,074
got inspiration

564
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:53,742
confused with love.

565
00:40:54,660 --> 00:40:57,705
An angel fell in love
with another being other than the deity?

566
00:40:58,372 --> 00:40:59,373
Is that possible?

567
00:41:33,365 --> 00:41:34,658
From this moment on...

568
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,160
No.

569
00:41:36,452 --> 00:41:38,537
From the very beginning,

570
00:41:39,371 --> 00:41:41,790
my love belonged to her.

571
00:41:42,583 --> 00:41:43,876
I believe that you're the one

572
00:41:44,793 --> 00:41:46,253
who helped us to meet

573
00:41:47,796 --> 00:41:49,089
and made us fall in love.

574
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:51,842
So please bless us.

575
00:41:54,637 --> 00:41:58,098
Believing that you can love something
other than the deity

576
00:41:58,599 --> 00:42:00,559
is an act of arrogance and sin.

577
00:42:03,103 --> 00:42:05,439
What happened to that angel then?

578
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:14,990
What do you think happened to an angel
who abandoned the deity?

579
00:42:21,413 --> 00:42:25,084
Angel Dan, receive your judgment.

580
00:42:26,126 --> 00:42:27,127
You dared to...

581
00:42:27,878 --> 00:42:29,004
I want to live.

582
00:42:29,296 --> 00:42:32,299
You dared to meddle in the life
that the deity had control over.

583
00:42:34,176 --> 00:42:35,469
I like you so much

584
00:42:36,387 --> 00:42:37,388
that it's driving me insane.

585
00:42:37,471 --> 00:42:41,100
You neglected and forgot
your mission, given to you by the deity.

586
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:43,060
By not carrying it out, you have sinned.

587
00:42:44,353 --> 00:42:45,354
Just look at me.

588
00:42:45,437 --> 00:42:48,566
Imagine that it's just
you and me in this world.

589
00:42:49,024 --> 00:42:49,984
Above all,

590
00:42:50,901 --> 00:42:52,444
you've deluded yourself into thinking

591
00:42:52,820 --> 00:42:55,698
that you loved an insignificant being
more than the deity.

592
00:42:57,283 --> 00:42:59,827
You will be dissipated.

593
00:43:46,373 --> 00:43:48,584
-Dan.
-Ma'am, what is it?

594
00:43:49,251 --> 00:43:50,544
It's been hours.

595
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:52,755
She's refusing to eat and
not letting anyone in.

596
00:44:52,189 --> 00:44:53,232
That's enough.

597
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:55,567
Don't overextend yourself.

598
00:45:05,285 --> 00:45:06,537
I said that's enough.

599
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:11,125
Did you forget?

600
00:45:11,583 --> 00:45:13,085
You shouldn't touch me.

601
00:45:17,423 --> 00:45:18,590
You're bleeding.

602
00:45:25,264 --> 00:45:26,181
So what?

603
00:45:30,686 --> 00:45:32,688
My toenails have fallen off many times.

604
00:45:32,855 --> 00:45:34,857
I've thrown away countless pairs
of bloody pointe shoes.

605
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,191
This is nothing.

606
00:45:43,532 --> 00:45:44,575
Finally,

607
00:45:45,617 --> 00:45:46,994
they look like a ballerina's feet.

608
00:45:56,086 --> 00:45:57,880
I didn't know you had to push yourself

609
00:45:59,548 --> 00:46:00,632
this much.

610
00:46:02,384 --> 00:46:03,886
You're going through so much pain.

611
00:46:07,848 --> 00:46:09,766
Let's call it a day, okay?

612
00:46:12,936 --> 00:46:14,229
Don't be ridiculous.

613
00:46:14,855 --> 00:46:16,148
I made a promise to Director Ji.

614
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:19,234
I have to get back in shape within a week.

615
00:46:22,779 --> 00:46:23,697
Listen to me.

616
00:46:23,780 --> 00:46:25,365
You can't continue
practicing with this foot.

617
00:46:25,574 --> 00:46:26,867
What if you get injured?

618
00:46:27,284 --> 00:46:30,287
Are you going to return to being someone
who's in solitude and grumpy?

619
00:46:30,370 --> 00:46:32,956
None of this matters if you're unhappy.

620
00:46:38,212 --> 00:46:39,338
I hate you.

621
00:46:40,714 --> 00:46:43,300
Don't be worried about me.
Don't care for me.

622
00:46:43,383 --> 00:46:44,343
I hate

623
00:46:46,136 --> 00:46:47,387
receiving love.

624
00:46:48,514 --> 00:46:50,098
It makes me want to become weak.

625
00:46:52,267 --> 00:46:55,103
It makes me think it is okay to be weak.

626
00:46:58,941 --> 00:47:00,400
I thought you liked me.

627
00:47:02,694 --> 00:47:03,570
I really did.

628
00:47:05,239 --> 00:47:06,782
You said you existed because of me.

629
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:09,952
You were the one who sweet-talked me.

630
00:47:10,786 --> 00:47:13,288
If you're neither a liar nor a spy,
then there's only one conclusion.

631
00:47:15,499 --> 00:47:16,542
Do you like me?

632
00:47:16,917 --> 00:47:20,045
Believing that you can love something
other than the deity

633
00:47:20,462 --> 00:47:22,631
is an act of arrogance and sin.

634
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:24,550
You said you couldn't lie.

635
00:47:25,801 --> 00:47:27,553
Just say yes or no.

636
00:47:29,638 --> 00:47:30,806
Did you like me?

637
00:47:33,934 --> 00:47:36,061
Do you?

638
00:47:47,281 --> 00:47:48,240
No.

639
00:47:57,916 --> 00:47:59,167
All right, then.

640
00:48:03,422 --> 00:48:04,464
Get lost.

641
00:48:37,414 --> 00:48:39,666
I had almost made a mistake,

642
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:42,002
but I am currently
carrying out my mission.

643
00:48:42,294 --> 00:48:43,295
This is Angel Dan.

644
00:48:46,757 --> 00:48:49,718
My subject has begun dancing once again.

645
00:48:51,386 --> 00:48:54,222
She is very sensitive and hot-tempered.

646
00:49:52,698 --> 00:49:54,700
I'm struggling alone without receiving

647
00:49:55,367 --> 00:49:56,827
any signs or prophecies.

648
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:17,139
At first, her temper was the problem.

649
00:50:18,098 --> 00:50:19,850
But now, she's too busy

650
00:50:21,017 --> 00:50:22,644
to love anyone.

651
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:25,981
Could there be a way

652
00:50:26,982 --> 00:50:30,402
for her to succeed
in both ballet and love?

653
00:50:32,863 --> 00:50:34,740
YEON-SEO'S GROWTH LOG

654
00:50:49,212 --> 00:50:50,714
YEONHWA ISLAND, 2005

655
00:50:50,797 --> 00:50:54,968
THE DAY I STARTED BALLET ONCE AGAIN!
MY FIRST STAGE AND MY FIRST AUDIENCE!

656
00:51:01,516 --> 00:51:03,226
You're unbelievable!

657
00:51:04,853 --> 00:51:05,771
Ms. Lee!

658
00:51:07,939 --> 00:51:08,857
Wake up.

659
00:51:09,649 --> 00:51:10,776
It's morning!

660
00:51:13,737 --> 00:51:15,572
What is the date today? What day is it?

661
00:51:15,739 --> 00:51:16,573
It's D-Day.

662
00:51:16,656 --> 00:51:18,825
It's been exactly a week
since your announcement.

663
00:51:21,953 --> 00:51:23,789
You shouldn't have stayed up
all night to practice.

664
00:51:23,872 --> 00:51:25,540
You get a zero for not
taking care of yourself.

665
00:51:31,087 --> 00:51:33,590
Your aunt called so
many times this morning.

666
00:51:35,801 --> 00:51:36,676
Look at this.

667
00:51:36,927 --> 00:51:38,428
She calls me every five minutes.

668
00:51:43,266 --> 00:51:44,267
It's me.

669
00:51:46,645 --> 00:51:47,604
Now?

670
00:51:56,321 --> 00:51:57,989
You didn't come with your secretary today.

671
00:51:58,865 --> 00:52:00,367
Please wait outside for me.

672
00:52:05,747 --> 00:52:08,250
You never answer my questions.

673
00:52:08,834 --> 00:52:10,544
How do you feel? Are you all right?

674
00:52:10,627 --> 00:52:11,753
Give me the withdrawal agreement

675
00:52:11,837 --> 00:52:13,380
on the power of attorney.
I brought my seal.

676
00:52:13,463 --> 00:52:15,549
My gosh, that's not ready yet.

677
00:52:15,632 --> 00:52:18,218
You said I had to sign it today.
That's why you told me to come out.

678
00:52:18,552 --> 00:52:19,594
Is that what you told her?

679
00:52:20,387 --> 00:52:23,390
My attorney is very meticulous.

680
00:52:23,473 --> 00:52:25,851
So my attorney needs to
check it a few more times.

681
00:52:26,268 --> 00:52:27,269
I'm sorry.

682
00:52:27,352 --> 00:52:29,187
-I'll get going then.
-Wait.

683
00:52:29,354 --> 00:52:32,190
Have some tea before you go.
I'm your aunt.

684
00:52:32,357 --> 00:52:34,651
We're not that close, you know.

685
00:52:34,734 --> 00:52:35,569
You must have been

686
00:52:36,069 --> 00:52:37,487
very disappointed in me.

687
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:40,115
To make up for that...

688
00:52:49,124 --> 00:52:52,210
-What's this?
-It's Fantasia's Night next week.

689
00:52:52,502 --> 00:52:53,753
Wear them to the event.

690
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:56,631
You know that I never
serve my guests at events.

691
00:52:56,798 --> 00:52:59,384
A very important Japanese
investor will be coming.

692
00:52:59,467 --> 00:53:01,553
When I told him your name,
he said he'd come.

693
00:53:01,887 --> 00:53:04,764
We can't hold the show
for your return without his money.

694
00:53:04,848 --> 00:53:07,100
Sometimes, you must do things
you don't want to.

695
00:53:07,183 --> 00:53:08,476
That's the world of adults.

696
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:10,854
We decided to announce
that everything related to Fantasia

697
00:53:11,438 --> 00:53:15,775
will belong to you at the
event that day in front of our sponsors.

698
00:53:20,989 --> 00:53:23,366
See how nice it is to start dancing again.

699
00:53:24,075 --> 00:53:27,120
You can walk with me like this
even without Dan.

700
00:53:28,997 --> 00:53:30,332
He has no place to go.

701
00:53:30,415 --> 00:53:31,666
Where did he go on his vacation?

702
00:53:33,835 --> 00:53:34,878
Well...

703
00:53:36,004 --> 00:53:37,005
What did he say?

704
00:53:37,130 --> 00:53:39,174
No. Don't tell me.

705
00:53:39,966 --> 00:53:41,843
Bosses who ask about
vacation spots are the worst.

706
00:53:44,346 --> 00:53:46,014
On the day of Fantasia's Night,

707
00:53:46,723 --> 00:53:49,142
I'll make him escort you no matter what.

708
00:53:51,519 --> 00:53:53,271
Let's hurry. I need to practice.

709
00:54:09,287 --> 00:54:11,790
I couldn't make him wait
at an empty house.

710
00:54:20,966 --> 00:54:24,094
This has been the longest week this year.

711
00:54:24,928 --> 00:54:25,929
Are you ready?

712
00:54:26,763 --> 00:54:28,848
No, not at all. I'm totally doomed.

713
00:54:29,849 --> 00:54:30,892
It's all a mess.

714
00:54:32,602 --> 00:54:33,478
Yeon-seo.

715
00:54:35,605 --> 00:54:36,439
What?

716
00:54:38,274 --> 00:54:40,151
Make yourself comfortable.
This will take long.

717
00:54:42,612 --> 00:54:44,531
-Where are we going?
-Well...

718
00:54:45,365 --> 00:54:46,491
To the beginning.

719
00:56:28,384 --> 00:56:29,427
This place...

720
00:56:29,511 --> 00:56:30,512
Do you remember?

721
00:56:31,387 --> 00:56:32,555
This feels familiar.

722
00:56:35,266 --> 00:56:36,267
What is this?

723
00:56:36,351 --> 00:56:38,937
What are you plotting?
Why did we come all the way here?

724
00:56:39,020 --> 00:56:40,021
In 2005,

725
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:42,232
right before you went to Russia
for your studies,

726
00:56:42,565 --> 00:56:45,193
you went to an island
for a program called Visiting Ballet.

727
00:56:45,819 --> 00:56:46,861
How do you know that?

728
00:56:47,153 --> 00:56:48,446
Did you look into my past?

729
00:56:51,533 --> 00:56:52,867
Dan told you, right?

730
00:56:53,576 --> 00:56:54,744
She never misses a thing.

731
00:56:55,453 --> 00:56:56,579
I bet

732
00:56:57,163 --> 00:56:58,456
Dan did everything here, right?

733
00:56:58,915 --> 00:56:59,999
Hey, Dan.

734
00:57:00,583 --> 00:57:01,918
Where are you? Come on out.

735
00:57:02,001 --> 00:57:04,504
Darn it. What's wrong with her?

736
00:57:05,547 --> 00:57:06,548
You're my prima ballerina.

737
00:57:06,631 --> 00:57:09,217
You don't think I would know
when you were born and how you grew up?

738
00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:16,558
I heard you hid and cried
because you didn't want to do ballet.

739
00:57:18,435 --> 00:57:20,437
I didn't know that. How did he know that?

740
00:57:23,231 --> 00:57:24,732
I knew a kid.

741
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:26,734
I've totally forgotten about the kid.

742
00:57:27,485 --> 00:57:28,403
That kid was

743
00:57:29,070 --> 00:57:30,071
my first audience.

744
00:57:31,906 --> 00:57:33,241
I danced for him.

745
00:57:34,534 --> 00:57:35,577
Just for him.

746
00:57:36,035 --> 00:57:36,911
Today,

747
00:57:37,412 --> 00:57:38,830
I'll watch your dance.

748
00:57:39,330 --> 00:57:41,166
The dance you did for your first audience.

749
00:57:41,666 --> 00:57:44,210
I don't remember. I didn't have
a routine because I was a kid.

750
00:57:50,550 --> 00:57:51,676
I can't make the turns.

751
00:57:55,388 --> 00:57:56,890
I can pull off other techniques

752
00:57:57,390 --> 00:57:59,517
once I get my muscles in shape
and practice more.

753
00:58:02,103 --> 00:58:03,313
But I can't make the turns.

754
00:58:05,940 --> 00:58:06,858
That's expected.

755
00:58:08,401 --> 00:58:10,737
You didn't dance for three years.
And it's been a week.

756
00:58:11,029 --> 00:58:12,572
Did you think I'd expect
you to be perfect?

757
00:58:13,281 --> 00:58:15,074
You're too confident of yourself.

758
00:58:18,411 --> 00:58:20,830
I wanted to see how determined you were.

759
00:58:23,166 --> 00:58:24,167
Your rhomboids,

760
00:58:24,667 --> 00:58:26,586
spinal erectors, and the soleus muscles.

761
00:58:27,128 --> 00:58:29,047
It took you a week to get them into shape.

762
00:58:29,923 --> 00:58:30,798
It's a miracle.

763
00:58:35,053 --> 00:58:36,846
Well said, Rib.

764
00:58:36,930 --> 00:58:37,972
Take it easy.

765
00:58:38,473 --> 00:58:40,934
Don't worry about turnout,
balance, or anything else.

766
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:42,268
Dance like your first time.

767
01:01:56,921 --> 01:01:58,214
Good news.

768
01:01:59,006 --> 01:02:00,717
It looks like cold-hearted Yeon-seo

769
01:02:01,509 --> 01:02:03,511
who was like an empty noisy gong,

770
01:02:04,637 --> 01:02:07,974
is finally about to start something.

771
01:02:09,559 --> 01:02:11,436
Her beginnings will seem humble,

772
01:02:12,228 --> 01:02:14,731
but love will be waiting for her
at the end, right?

773
01:02:16,524 --> 01:02:18,359
I am about to finish my mission.

774
01:02:19,944 --> 01:02:20,778
But

775
01:02:22,071 --> 01:02:23,406
why is my heart

776
01:02:24,615 --> 01:02:25,616
in so much pain?

777
01:02:44,719 --> 01:02:45,845
Why are you crying?

778
01:02:48,139 --> 01:02:49,307
Were you disappointed?

779
01:02:53,561 --> 01:02:54,562
That was so pretty.

780
01:02:55,980 --> 01:02:58,483
That was the prettiest thing
I've ever seen.

781
01:03:41,400 --> 01:03:42,902
You're smiling brightly, aren't you?

782
01:03:44,946 --> 01:03:45,780
You look pretty.

783
01:03:45,863 --> 01:03:47,657
Don't you think this was a bit too much?

784
01:03:47,740 --> 01:03:49,158
"She was beautiful.

785
01:03:49,242 --> 01:03:51,702
It was the prettiest thing"

786
01:03:51,786 --> 01:03:52,995
It's the truth!

787
01:03:53,079 --> 01:03:53,996
I'll fight with you.

788
01:03:54,080 --> 01:03:57,250
I want to see you become the center
of Fantasia.

789
01:03:57,917 --> 01:03:59,752
Think about how the chandelier fell.

790
01:04:00,169 --> 01:04:01,128
I'm just worried.

791
01:04:01,879 --> 01:04:05,007
You save me and help me out.

792
01:04:05,299 --> 01:04:07,051
But why don't you like me?

793
01:04:07,426 --> 01:04:10,137
How can I not like you?

